CONTRIBUTING.md
     1вҶ’# Contributing
     3вҶ’## Issues
     5вҶ’New issues are welcome, whether questions or suggestions or reporting bugs.
     6вҶ’You are also welcome to contribute by adding helpful comments on an existing issue.
     7вҶ’
     8вҶ’We love reproducible code examples in questions and answers.
     9вҶ’
    10вҶ’If you get a satisfactory reply to a question then please close your issue, but it is ok to leave an issue open for more replies or interest. Inactive issues may get closed after one month if they have an answer,
    11вҶ’or after six months otherwise.
    12вҶ’
    13вҶ’## Pull Requests
    15вҶ’Pull Requests will be considered. Please submit pull requests against the develop branch.
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’Follow the existing code style. Check the tests succeed, including format and lint.
    18вҶ’
    19вҶ’- `npm run test`
    20вҶ’- `npm run check`
    21вҶ’
    22вҶ’Don't update the CHANGELOG or command version number. That gets done by maintainers when preparing the release.
    23вҶ’
    24вҶ’Useful things to include in your request description are:
    25вҶ’
    26вҶ’- what problem are you solving?
    27вҶ’- what Issues does this relate to?
    28вҶ’- suggested summary for CHANGELOG
    29вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
Readme.md
   968вҶ’### .parse() and .parseAsync()
   970вҶ’Call with no parameters to parse `process.argv`. Detects Electron and special node options like `node --eval`. Easy mode!
   971вҶ’
   972вҶ’Or, call with an array of strings to parse, and optionally where the user arguments start by specifying where the arguments are `from`:
   973вҶ’
   974вҶ’- `'node'`: default, `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` is the script being run, with user arguments after that
   975вҶ’- `'electron'`: `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` varies depending on whether the electron application is packaged
   976вҶ’- `'user'`: just user arguments
   977вҶ’
   978вҶ’For example:
   979вҶ’
   980вҶ’```js
   981вҶ’program.parse(); // parse process.argv and auto-detect electron and special node flags
   982вҶ’program.parse(process.argv); // assume argv[0] is app and argv[1] is script
   983вҶ’program.parse(['--port', '80'], { from: 'user' }); // just user supplied arguments, nothing special about argv[0]
   984вҶ’```
   985вҶ’
   986вҶ’Use `.parseAsync()` instead of `.parse()` if any of your action handlers are async.
   987вҶ’
Readme_zh-CN.md
   907вҶ’### .parse() е’Ң .parseAsync()
   909вҶ’`.parse`зҡ„з¬¬дёҖдёӘеҸӮж•°жҳҜиҰҒи§Јжһҗзҡ„еӯ—з¬ҰдёІж•°з»„пјҢд№ҹеҸҜд»ҘзңҒз•ҘеҸӮж•°иҖҢдҪҝз”Ё`process.argv`гҖӮ
   910вҶ’
   911вҶ’еҰӮжһңеҸӮж•°йҒөеҫӘдёҺ node дёҚеҗҢзҡ„зәҰе®ҡпјҢеҸҜд»ҘеңЁз¬¬дәҢдёӘеҸӮж•°дёӯдј йҖ’`from`йҖүйЎ№пјҡ
   912вҶ’
   913вҶ’- `node`пјҡй»ҳи®ӨеҖјпјҢ`argv[0]`жҳҜеә”з”ЁпјҢ`argv[1]`жҳҜиҰҒи·‘зҡ„и„ҡжң¬пјҢеҗҺз»ӯдёәз”ЁжҲ·еҸӮж•°пјӣ
   914вҶ’- `electron`пјҡ`argv[1]`ж №жҚ® electron еә”з”ЁжҳҜеҗҰжү“еҢ…иҖҢеҸҳеҢ–пјӣ
   915вҶ’- `user`пјҡжқҘиҮӘз”ЁжҲ·зҡ„жүҖжңүеҸӮж•°гҖӮ
   916вҶ’
   917вҶ’дҫӢеҰӮпјҡ
   918вҶ’
   919вҶ’```js
   920вҶ’program.parse(process.argv); // жҢҮжҳҺпјҢжҢү node зәҰе®ҡ
   921вҶ’program.parse(); // й»ҳи®ӨпјҢиҮӘеҠЁиҜҶеҲ« electron
      вҶ’вҖҰ
SECURITY.md
     1вҶ’# Security Policy
     3вҶ’To report a security vulnerability, please use the
     4вҶ’[Tidelift security contact](https://tidelift.com/security).
     5вҶ’Tidelift will coordinate the fix and disclosure.
     6вҶ’
     7вҶ’Please do not report security vulnerabilities through public GitHub issues or pull requests.
docs/deprecated.md
   229вҶ’### Short option flag longer than a single character
   231вҶ’Short option flags like `-ws` were never supported, but the old README did not make this clear. The README now states that short options are a single character.
   232вҶ’
   233вҶ’- README updated in Commander v3.
   234вҶ’- Deprecated from Commander v9.
   235вҶ’- Throws an exception in Commander v13. Deprecated and gone!
   236вҶ’- Replacement added in Commander v13.1 with support for dual long options, like `--ws, --workspace`.
   237вҶ’
